cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL 

This paper is about generating keyphrases for a given document using neural networks. The task involves natural language processing and information retrieval, which are the main topics of the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The paper also discusses unsupervised keyphrase extraction methods, which falls under the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. The use of semi-supervised learning and multi-task learning frameworks are common in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses neural networks for training, which is a common technique in the cs.DL (Deep Learning) sub-category.
